It’s hard to believe it’s been 3 years since my dad passed. Sometimes it feels like an eternity. And sometimes I can still feel his big hugs and how he’d tear up every time he heard me sing, even just in the living room. I miss him every day and I’m so grateful that I know he’s close by and I can listen to his music any time. What an incredible blessing that is. Our deep love of music keeps us forever close together and I’ll be recording today and doing what we both loved most in his honor. I miss you daddy and I know you’re up there watching over me and sprinkling your one of a kind, Texas Red magic on my life and my career so I can do the thing we were both put here to do… sing, entertain, and live a damn good life!

The best feeling ever is that I’m always the most excited to spend time with my wife. We have the most fun no matter what we’re doing! Tonight it was going to an artist talk and a private collectors dinner. Tomorrow it will be going to Trader Joe’s to get dog treats for our floofy boy! 💙🩵✈️🐾

Daddy, miss you every day and in a million more ways than I ever knew possible. I know you’re watching over me and I can feel your musical magic working as I see the opportunities that are opening up before me. Music will always be the red thread that bonds us beyond all space and time. And I’ll keep singing until we can sing together again, but I know you’ll be looking out for me and with me at every show. 💡💡🎹🎹🎤🎤💙🩵 Happy Father’s Day!

The chop! ✂️ I firmly believe hair can hold a lot of trauma. I started growing my hair out during the pandemic for our wedding. 💕 During that time my dad passed away and I ultimately experienced a very deep depression for several months. I’ve been in an incredible place of healing the past few months and this was the next right step. I feel lighter in a million ways. Didn’t have quite enough length to donate to Locks of Love this time, but I look forward to donating my hair the next time I grow it out and cut it. 💙 Heal however you need to. People don’t need to understand, the right people will be there to support you and accept what you’re dealing with. Surround yourself with comfort and love if you’re in a healing process. It gets better, and everything really will be okay. ➡️ Before pic and the massive amount of hair cut! Gratitude for @hairxjc @bellasalonatx for the wonderful cut!
